    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "07f57393_35acffe8",
        "filename": "util/misc/range_set.h",
        "patchSetId": 16
      },
      "lineNbr": 42,
      "author": {
        "id": 1144260
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-06-01T05:02:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "With my newly discovered excitement about fuzzing in https://bugs.chromium.org/p/crashpad/issues/detail?id\u003d233 I hacked a fuzzer and range_set into https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1081587.\n\nUnfortunately it found that the ranges can become overlapping:\n\n\tranges.Insert(37, 16);\n\tranges.Insert(9, 9);\n\tranges.Insert(17, 42);\n\nwill, I think, result in ranges_ storing two overlapping ranges: (37..53) and (9..59).\n\n(I\u0027m still not 100% sure if this breaks this code, but I think it might since Contains() could find the wrong range, right?)",
      "parentUuid": "ad14b31f_36ef1dbe",
      "revId": "13a8b4352e73784300e1a0e07ffe0cdcce54bc97",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9d57ce82_830e368a",
        "filename": "util/misc/range_set.h",
        "patchSetId": 16
      },
      "lineNbr": 42,
      "author": {
        "id": 1172779
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-06-01T17:17:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah, overlapping ranges would break Contains() if it found the wrong range.\nI think I was making this too complicated. I went with something similar to Tobias\u0027s option #2. This new strategy iterates from `base` to `last`, removing all overlapping ranges, and growing the range to insert as it iterates. Adjacent, non-overlapping ranges above get merged, but not adjacent below. Finish by inserting the new merged range.",
      "parentUuid": "07f57393_35acffe8",
      "revId": "13a8b4352e73784300e1a0e07ffe0cdcce54bc97",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
